  <h1>VRI™ Connect</h1>

  <div class="subtitle">
    VRI™ Connect allows companies to plug verification, proof records, receipts, and audit trails into the systems they already use.
    Companies do not have to replace their current platforms. VRI™ adds a proof layer on top of them.
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <strong>Core Positioning:</strong><br><br>
    VRI™ is not just a portal. It is verification infrastructure. It helps companies prove who did what, when it happened,
    what was submitted, what was verified, and what receipt or audit trail was created.
  </div>

  <h2>Who VRI™ Connect Is For</h2>

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="card">Law firms and legal document workflows</div>
    <div class="card">Healthcare systems and patient action tracking</div>
    <div class="card">Financial companies and transaction verification</div>
    <div class="card">Government contractors and compliance records</div>
    <div class="card">HR departments and employee verification</div>
    <div class="card">AI platforms needing proof and governance</div>
  </div>

  <h2>What Companies Can Verify</h2>

  <div class="card">
    <span class="badge">People</span>
    <span class="badge">Businesses</span>
    <span class="badge">Documents</span>
    <span class="badge">Emails</span>
    <span class="badge">Phone Numbers</span>
    <span class="badge">Payments</span>
    <span class="badge">Messages</span>
    <span class="badge">AI Content</span>
    <span class="badge">Employee Actions</span>
    <span class="badge">System Events</span>
  </div>

  <h2>Ways Companies Can Plug In</h2>

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="card">
      <strong>1. Manual Portal Access</strong><br>
      A company logs into VRI™ and manually creates proof records.
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <strong>2. Embedded Verification Form</strong><br>
      A company places a VRI™ verification form inside its own website or dashboard.
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <strong>3. API Connection</strong><br>
      A company system sends proof data directly to VRI™ automatically.
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <strong>4. Webhook Trigger</strong><br>
      A company event triggers VRI™ to create a proof record, receipt, and audit trail.
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <strong>5. SDK / Developer Package</strong><br>
      A developer package allows companies to install VRI™ proof functions into their own app.
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <strong>6. White-Label Verification Portal</strong><br>
      A company uses a branded verification experience powered by VRI™ behind the scenes.
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>How the VRI™ Connection Flow Works</h2>

  <div class="flow">
    Company System<br>
    → sends verification data to VRI™<br>
    → VRI™ creates Proof ID<br>
    → VRI™ stores proof record<br>
    → VRI™ logs verification events<br>
    → VRI™ generates receipt<br>
    → Company receives proof status and audit trail
  </div>

  <h2>What VRI™ Creates</h2>

  <div class="card">
    Every connected proof can generate:
    <br><br>
    - Proof ID<br>
    - Business Name Record<br>
    - Verification Intent<br>
    - Document Record<br>
    - Recipient Record<br>
    - Verification Events<br>
    - Receipt Record<br>
    - Timestamped Audit Trail<br>
    - Monitor Activity
  </div>

  <h2>Company Plug-In Function</h2>

  <div class="card">
    VRI™ includes a company plug-in function that allows external systems to create proof records.
    This means outside platforms can send structured verification data into VRI™ and receive a proof result.
    <br><br>
    This supports the long-term API model, company dashboards, connected systems, and enterprise verification workflows.
  </div>

  <h2>Security and Access Control</h2>

  <div class="card">
    Future company access will include:
    <br><br>
    - Company ID tracking<br>
    - API key authentication<br>
    - Connected system logs<br>
    - Permission-based access<br>
    - Proof ownership by company<br>
    - Verification monitoring by account
  </div>

  <h2>Developer Access Coming Soon</h2>

  <div class="card">
    Developer access will allow companies to connect through:
    <br><br>
    - API endpoint<br>
    - Webhook endpoint<br>
    - JavaScript SDK<br>
    - Embedded verification widget<br>
    - White-label proof portal<br>
    - Company dashboard
  </div>

  <h2>Why This Matters</h2>

  <div class="card">
    VRI™ gives companies a way to prove digital actions before trust breaks down.
    In a world of AI-generated content, fake records, identity concerns, disputed communications, and unclear accountability,
    VRI™ creates a receipt-backed proof layer for modern systems.
  </div>

  <h2>Enterprise Positioning</h2>

  <div class="card">
    VRI™ is designed to become a universal verification and receipt intelligence layer for legal, healthcare, finance,
    government, HR, SaaS, and AI-powered platforms.
    <br><br>
    It helps companies answer one critical question:
    <br><br>
    <strong>Who did what, when did it happen, and what proof exists?</strong>
  </div>

